For Task 1 of my Digital Literacy project I used Canva to create an infographic called "DIGITAL LITERACY: YOUR SUPERPOWER". This infographic is about Digital Literacy.

The topic of this infographic is Digital Literacy. The design explains what Digital Literacy is about. It breaks down Digital Literacy into four parts.

First it explains what Digital Literacy means. Digital Literacy means using Digital Literacy to think and use information in a responsible way. It is not about using apps.

Second it talks about " TOOLS FOR STUDENTS". These tools are really important for students. The tools I listed are Notion, Google Docs, Grammarly, Canva and ChatGPT. These tools help students organize their notes and write better.

Third it talks about "STAY SAFE ONLINE". This part is about being safe on the internet. It tells people to use passwords and be careful of fake emails.

Finally it talks about "BUILD YOUR DIGITAL IDENTITY". This part is about making a profile. It tells people to use email and make profiles.

One big challenge I faced was making it short and simple. I had to make topics like cybersecurity and professional branding short and easy to understand. I had to choose my words. Digital Literacy is really important. I had to use pictures and words to help people understand what Digital Literacy is, about.
